The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning approach for high-level driving behavior decision-making in heterogeneous traffic scenarios. This involves the use of a data preprocessor, deep neural network, and simulation environment. The paper falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the use of deep reinforcement learning. It also involves the use of deep neural networks (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for feature extraction. The simulation environment and the use of reinforcement learning for decision-making also suggest that the paper could fall under robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
